# release-scan allowlist — paths excluded from the branch-safety scan because they
# legitimately contain secret-shaped or pattern-describing content, NOT real
# secrets. One git pathspec glob per line; `#` comments. COMMITTED and reviewed:
# a reviewer sees exactly which paths are exempt from secret scanning.
#
# Keep this surgical — only internal (non-shipped-as-product) paths known to
# contain fixtures or pattern documentation.

# Hermetic tests deliberately embed fake AWS/GitHub-shaped secrets as fixtures.
scripts/test-workflow-scripts.mjs

# The scanner's own source and docs literally contain the secret regexes it matches.
plugins/workaholic/skills/release-scan/**

# ...and build.mjs copies that source verbatim into the generated bundles, so the
# generated mirror needs the same exemption as the source it is generated FROM.
# Without this the scanner blocks any branch that touches its own patterns — the file
# defining the denylist matches the denylist.
outputs/workflows/skills/*/release-scan/**

# The engine ticket documents the credential / internal-hostname patterns in prose.
.workaholic/tickets/**/*release-scan*

# Same reason, for the story that narrates the false-positive fix: prose describing the
# rule cannot avoid the rule -- even ordinary English phrasing parses as an assignment,
# and the illustrations are the very shapes under discussion. Exempted by exact path,
# not `stories/**` -- a story can legitimately carry a pasted credential, so stories
# stay scanned by default.
.workaholic/stories/work-20260714-222630.md

# NOTE: keep this file's own comments free of key-shaped examples. It is scanned like any
# other committed file and cannot sensibly exempt itself -- and it never needs to, since
# it holds paths, not patterns.
